												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/aysegulsert/">Aysegul Sert</a></h6>
													Born and raised in Istanbul, fluent in four languages, Ayşegül Sert has reported extensively from Turkey, France, and the United States. Her articles are published in <em>The New York Times</em>, <em>Le Figaro</em>, <em>Le Monde</em>, and <em>The New Yorker</em>. An advocate for writers at risk, her work focuses on freedom of speech, gender equality, and human rights. She is a guest commentator on Arte and France Culture on issues related to international politics and culture.																									</div>
